org.spongepowered.api.data.value.immutable

Interface ImmutableListValue<E>

  • Type Parameters:
    E - The type of element of this list value
    All Superinterfaces:
    BaseValue<List<E>>, ImmutableCollectionValue<E,List<E>,ImmutableListValue<E>,ListValue<E>>, ImmutableValue<List<E>>
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    ImmutablePatternListValue

    public interface ImmutableListValue<E>
extends ImmutableCollectionValue<E,List<E>,ImmutableListValue<E>,ListValue<E>>
    A type of ImmutableCollectionValue that is backed by a List. All "with" and "Without" methods are returning new instances as every instance is immutable.

                           E value)

      • with

        ImmutableListValue<E> with(int index,
                           Iterable<E> values)
        Creates a new ImmutableListValue with the specified elements in the order that they are iterated to the list at the specified index. The element at the provided index and elements thereafter are shifted to the right, increasing their indices by one.
        Parameters:

        values - The elements to add
        Returns:
        The new value, for chaining

      • without

        ImmutableListValue<E> without(int index)
        Creates a new ImmutableListValue without the element at the specified index. Shifts any subsequent elements to the left, subtracts one from their indices.
        Parameters:
        index - The index of the element to exclude
        Returns:
        The new value, for chaining
